the extensor and flexor group of the thigh', 'start': 15.23, 'duration': 5.81}, {'text': 'muscles.', 'start': 21.04, 'duration': 1.0}, {'text': 'The hip adductors shape the surface anatomy
of the medial thigh.', 'start': 22.04, 'duration': 7.52}, {'text': 'The innervation is mainly supplied by the
obturator nerve which arises from the lumbar', 'start': 29.56, 'duration': 4.72}, {'text': 'plexus and reaches the adductors through the

and the linea aspera of the femur.', 'start': 49.1, 'duration': 5.72}, {'text': 'It is additionally innervated by the femoral
nerve.', 'start': 54.82, 'duration': 6.919}, {'text': 'The adductor magnus muscle is one of the biggest

fleshy insertion, and the medial epicondyle', 'start': 72.639, 'duration': 5.741}, {'text': 'tendinous insertion.', 'start': 78.38, 'duration': 1.689}, {'text': 'The superficial part of the adductor magnus
is supplied by the tibial nerve.', 'start': 80.069, 'duration': 8.221}, {'text': 'The adductor longus muscle has its origin
at the superior pubic ramus and the pubic', 'start': 88.29, 'duration': 4.98}, {'text': 'symphysis and insertion at the linea aspera.', 'start': 93.27, 'duration': 3.12}, {'text': 'Distally, it forms an aponeurosis extending
to the vastus medialis muscle.', 'start': 96.39, 'duration': 9.429}, {'text': 'The adductor brevis muscle originates at the
inferior pubic ramus and inserts at the linea', 'start': 105.819, 'duration': 5.54}, {'text': 'aspera.', 'start': 111.359, 'duration': 5.19}, {'text': 'And the adductor minimus muscle describes
the inconstant cranial separation of the adductor', 'start': 116.549, 'duration': 5.511}, {'text': 'magnus which is found in many people.', 'start': 122.06, 'duration': 3.009}, {'text': 'It extends from the inferior pubic ramus to
the linea aspera.', 'start': 125.069, 'duration': 8.241}, {'text': 'The gracilis muscle runs from the inferior
border of the pubic symphysis to the superficial', 'start': 133.31, 'duration': 5.61}, {'text': 'pes anserinus of the tibia.', 'start': 138.92, 'duration': 2.87}, {'text': 'Its tendon is easy to palpate in the inguinal
region, together with the tendon of the adductor', 'start': 141.79, 'duration': 5.57}, {'text': 'longus muscle.', 'start': 147.36, 'duration': 4.61}, {'text': 'Both the femoral artery and vein as well as

insertion of the adductor magnus and leads', 'start': 171.81, 'duration': 6.38}, {'text': 'to the popliteal fossa.', 'start': 178.19, 'duration': 3.43}, {'text': 'As the name suggests, the main function of

– pectineus, adductor brevis, and adductor', 'start': 189.53, 'duration': 5.93}, {'text': 'magnus; inward rotation – tendinous insertion

muscle moves the knee joint as well where', 'start': 207.08, 'duration': 6.05}, {'text': 'its contraction causes a flexion and inward
